latestIgtvVideos.title: Eyebrow shaping painless method 💛
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I'm always used to threading or tweezing my brows by myself. Since I'm carrying now I had to switch to painless way to shape my brows. I had actually let them grow for 4 months without shaping them. So I tried this method of using a facial razor and shaping my brows. Initially it is tough but it gets easier with time. Be a little extra cautious so that you don't slide them on your brows or lashes 🙈 It's super easy top of your brows but the inner side becomes tough. The trick is to slide them at 45° opposite direction of hair growth. They snip of easily. No pain 👌 Use a scissors to maintain the proper length. Use astringent after shaping if you have sensitive skin 💛

latestIgtvVideos.title: How to shape brows perfectly at home 💛
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
My brow routine. Ever since the lockdown I stopped getting my brows done at the salon and started doing on my own. 

Things you need

💛 Pair of tweezers @kandditbeauty

💛 Facial razor @tinklerazors

💛 Brow filler @maccosmeticsindia

💛 Concealer @lagirlindia

So first you start off with a clean face. Apply powder on and below brows. Using my tweezers I start pulling out each strand that is out of place. Then with a STEADY hand I shave the upper area of my brows with the facial razor for a clean shape. Now I wipe it off and use a brow pomade to fill in all the gaps. Then use a concealer to highlight your brow bone and voila Defined brows 😍

.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Indian wedding guest make up look 😍
How to chose a concealer that perfectly matches 👌
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Read the full caption 😘
First of all a concealer has a better coverage than a foundation and is used to conceal, cover spots, pimples, to brighten and to contour. Sometimes a color corrector is also called a concealer. Green corrector to cover redness. Orange corrector to cover black spots or intense dark circles. Yellow to brighten. 
So the trick I personally use is to use a concealer 1 shade darker than my skin tone to cover uneven areas. Apply the concealer on areas that are darker than your actual skin color and blended. Then use a foundation on top of it for the entire face (Foundation can be skipped) I use a concealer 1 shade lighter than my skin to brighten the high points, you can also try a yellow concealer if you have a warm undertone. If you want to contour then use a super dark brown shade atleast 3-4 shades darker than your skin and contour 😘 Now the finishing part 😚 Set it allll with powder. You are good to go with a tint of lip balm or lipstick 💄 
I usually use this method to match my concealer cuz I do not like the orangeness of the corrector. To decide on the shade to buy visually pick 4 shades closest to your skin tone. Now swatch the 4 shades against your cheek and decide 💛 
.
.

Rasnadi churnam 💛 Works like magic. Came to know about this powder during my postpartum ayurvedic retreat. My kids were prone to cough and cold prior to this(because they are premature and immunity is less compared to full term babies). But for the past 4 months my twins haven’t got cold. 🧿( touchwood) This is a ayurvedic powder called Rasnadi chooranam you can get from any naturopathy or ayurvedic shop or Amazon. It’s a soft brown powder that has a mild herbal fragrance to it. You just need to gently place a pinch of this powder on baby bregma (soft spot on the head) after their head shower. It has to placed very softly like feather touch and no pressing! I place it twice a week after their bath. If they are sneezing or feel like they are about to catch cold then I place everyday. It subsides in 2 days. It’s used only externally so you need not worry that it might affect the baby. Please feel free to check with your doctor also. Prior to this I was using nasal saline drops to control cold but I felt this is so much better and easier way to PREVENT and as well as control cold. This can be used for adults also. For new moms too on the day you take a head shower. It has to be placed on the head where we call Uchi or 6 fingers from your forehead. It absolutely works like magic. I was genuinely surprised when I came to know about this and was wondering why not many know about this. So tried to make a video of this. Hope it helps 💛 Incase of doubts please leave them in the comments ✨ Will respond in a day’s time 💛 Thank you for understanding my time constraints 🙏 Comment "💛" for link
